@startuml UC-005: Monitor Grading Progress in Real-time

title UC-005: Monitor Grading Progress in Real-time
autonumber

actor Student
participant "Client" as Client
participant "Submission API\n(Elysia)" as API
participant "SSE Service" as SSE
participant "Grading Service\n(FastAPI)" as Grader
database "MongoDB" as DB

== Open SSE Connection ==
Student -> Client: View submission progress
Client -> API: GET /v0/submissions/:jobId/stream
API -> SSE: addClient(jobId, stream)
SSE --> API: Client registered
API --> Client: SSE connection established
Client --> Student: Show progress UI (0%)

== Grading Started ==
Grader -> API: POST /v0/submissions/started
API -> DB: Update submission (status: running)
DB --> API: Updated
API -> SSE: sendStarted(jobId, "Grading started")
SSE --> Client: event: started\ndata: {status: "running"}
Client --> Student: Update progress (5%) "Initializing..."

== Task Progress Updates ==
loop For each task
    Grader -> Grader: Execute task (ping/command/NAPALM)
    Grader -> API: POST /v0/submissions/progress
    API -> DB: Append progress to history
    DB --> API: Updated
    API -> SSE: sendProgress(jobId, progress)
    SSE --> Client: event: progress\ndata: {percentage: 35%, message: "Task 3/10"}
    Client --> Student: Update progress bar and message
end

== Grading Completed ==
Grader -> API: POST /v0/submissions/result
API -> DB: Update submission (status: completed, results)
DB --> API: Updated
API -> SSE: sendResult(jobId, gradingResult)
SSE --> Client: event: completed\ndata: {points: 85/100, test_results: [...]}
Client --> Student: Show final results (100%)

SSE -> SSE: Close connection after 500ms
SSE --> Client: Connection closed
Client -> Client: Redirect to results page

@enduml
